data.enText: dishonest behaviour that is intended to make sb believe sth that is not true; an example of this behaviour
He was accused of lies and deceit.

data.chText: 所有人都牵涉到这起诈骗勾当之中了。
data.enText: Everyone was involved in this web of deceit.

data.chText: 他们的婚姻是虚假的，不真实的。
data.enText: Their marriage was an illusion and a deceit.

value.def: Deceit is behaviour that is deliberately intended to make people believe something which is not true.

example.ex: They have been involved in a campaign of deceit.
example.tran: 他们参与了一系列的欺骗活动。
